Sentencas: Highly active and stable cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) are vital to develop intermediatetemperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here we report a novel class of cathodes with B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+delta (SCNxF, x = 0.0-0.2).
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SCNxF oxides have a single-phase cubic structure and good structural stability and chemical compatibility with La0.9Sr0.1-Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) and Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 electrolytes.
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Nb doping improves the thermodynamical stability and the thermal expansion compatibility of the SCNxF materials as compared to the undoped Sr2CoFeO5+delta.
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistances of SCNxF cathodes with x = 0.0, 0.1, and 0.2 on the LSGM electrolyte are 0.048, 0.081, and 0.174 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Also the SCN0.1F cathode shows better cell performance and electrochemical stability in the practical SOFC.
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The findings indicate that the SCN0.1F is a promising cathode material of IT-SOFCs with high electrocatalytic activity for ORR, functional stability, and high electrical conductivity.
Titulo: B-site-ordered Co-based double perovskites Sr2Co1-xNbxFeO5+δ as active and stable cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
